{
  "stem": "10572.6",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But even today, I feel that my business was much more serious than some know-wells' business ever could have been.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then I left England on the 1st of May from Liverpool and got on a ship.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We didn't know the name, but it had anti-aircraft guns on top of the ship because we were going through submarine-infested waters.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the first four days and four nights, we slept and ate and walked with our life belts on in order to-- and the ship that took us across the ocean was the Britannic of the Cunard White Star Line, which we found out later on.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we were on the sea, and we traveled in a zig-zag to escape them.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And after four or five days, we were out of danger.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then on the 10th of May, there was a note at the postal office that Belgium, Luxembourg, and Holland had fallen.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And when I arrived in America, I had $28 in my pockets, 10 pounds.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I had 10 pounds.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And the people in New York were so doubtful about the survival of Great Britain that I had a tough time changing the 10 pounds into dollars.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And then I was in America.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The-- one of the things that struck me, the obvious, was after blackout and after complete blackout and darkness, we came to the city with light and light and light.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I had never seen skyscraper, and here were these skyscrapers and thousands of cars driving up and down.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And people, fast talking, all somehow seemed to have a goal in life.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I was arriving, and I didn't know which way to turn.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I didn't have any [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I didn't have any people that I knew that I could go to, with the exception that there was a old friend of mine from Hamburg who used a pharmacy-- used to own a pharmacy in-- in-- in-- in-- in Hamburg.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He and his wife were at the boat to pick me up, and they took me to their house in Weehawken, New Jersey.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "For the first couple of days, I stayed with them until I found a job.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I went-- I arrived on a Saturday, and I went to Fifth Avenue on Monday morning and started working for a very fine custom tailor near Saint Patrick's Cathedral, Shiner Limited, on Wednesday morning.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And then when things started, when the temperature got hot in New York, they told me that they were closing up because all of their customers went to the sea and into the mountains.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they would reopen on-- after Labor Day, I could have my job back.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But in the meantime, I had to live.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I had been-- it was stupid of me-- too proud to go to an aid agency.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I had felt that I was now on my own.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And after I was there for about four weeks, I got a letter from my father that they needed $700 for the passage, for the steamship, because the American steamship lines wouldn't accept the German money anymore.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And so I thought in those days that the problems of yesterday became very small with the problems that I had to face then.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I was without a job.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I had to wait until after Labor Day, if I could survive that long.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then I finally buried my pride and went to a Jewish aid-- the refugee committee.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they told me that they wanted to get me out of New York.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was a concentration, and they wanted to disperse us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And would I be willing to go to Elkhart, Indiana?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I was at that point ready to go anywhere.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I went on the Greyhound Bus to Elkhart, Indiana.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there was a wonderful guy, met me the Greyhound Bus Station, Orry-- Orry Goldberg, who owned the men's store in town.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he was Mr.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Refugee Committee.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He greeted me.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the shock was kind of tremendous, after New York-- Elkhart.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Anybody who has ever been in Elkhart, Indiana-- and I wasn't quite sure if I had been so wise to survive Buchenwald to end up in Elkhart.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The heat of the summer, slept with the-- without any air conditioner-- any.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was pretty horrible.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And about a week later, a letter was forward to me from Palm Springs, California, Mrs.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Hamilton, with a check in it for $700 as a loan so that I could buy the passage for my parents.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I took that as an indication of the earlier imperative, go west, young man.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I got on the bus and had told Orry Goldberg that I was leaving Elkhart.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
